column75: RT1   All prescriptions are created and transmitted electronically when they are generated. All prescriptions are queried for a drug formulary automatically when they are generated. Therefore, the numerator will always be equal to the denominator; RT2  automatically makes patient data available to an API since the API calls directly access the database. Therefore, Section of Stage 3  Patient Health Information is available to access via API within 48 hours will always equal to Yes;  RT5 ehrTHOMAS does not have the ability to allow a patient to be copied on a secure message;  RT10, 11, 12 All medication, lab, and radiology orders entered into ehrTHOMAS are considered CPOE.  Therefore, the numerator will always be equal to the denominator.
